---
title: BLKB System Architecture
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as blkb_client.py
    participant S as btk_server.py<br/>(GLib main loop)
    participant D as D-Bus<br/>org.bluez
    participant HCI as Bluetooth<br/>HCI layer
    participant H as Host (Windows)

    Note over C,S: Unix socket /tmp/blkb.sock
    C->>S: type hello\n
    S-->>C: OK\n

    Note over S,H: L2CAP PSM 17 (Control) + PSM 19 (Interrupt)
    S->>S: queue command
    S->>S: type_next(): send_key_down(mod, scancode)
    S->>S: type_up(): send_key_up()
    S->>H: HID Input Report (PSM 19)

    Note over S,D: Setup Phase
    S->>D: org.bluez.Adapter1.Set(Powered, Discoverable, Pairable)
    S->>D: org.bluez.AgentManager1.RegisterAgent(DisplayOnly)
    S->>D: org.bluez.ProfileManager1.RegisterProfile(HID UUID)
    S->>HCI: hciconfig class 0x0025C0

    Note over H,S: Pairing Phase
    H->>HCI: L2CAP Connection Request (PSM 1 for SDP)
    HCI->>S: IO Capability Request
    S->>HCI: IO Capability (DisplayOnly)
    H->>HCI: SDP ServiceSearch Request
    S->>HCI: SDP Response (HID record + others)
    H->>HCI: Simple Pairing Complete (Just Works)

    Note over H,S: HID Connection Phase
    H->>HCI: L2CAP Connection Request (PSM 17)
    S->>HCI: Accept
    H->>S: HIDP GET_REPORT / SET_PROTOCOL
    S->>H: HIDP Response

    H->>HCI: L2CAP Connection Request (PSM 19)
    S->>HCI: Accept
    S->>H: HID Input Reports (keystrokes)
